@ChuckReynolds If your home page is a static page it will prob do that. Maybe check is_front_page() || is_home() first and then do elseif
@ChuckReynolds @johnjamesjacoby But a CPT is not a post post type like you're checking there, it's either hierarchical or it's not.
@ChuckReynolds or !is_post_type_hierarchical, whichever way it goes
@ChuckReynolds Still think your line 114 could just be if (is_singular() && is_post_type_hierarchical( get_post_type() ) ) instead.
@ChuckReynolds @johnjamesjacoby That sounds backward. Posts are not hierarchical.
@ChuckReynolds @norcross Why do you need to leave the post post type in there? is_post_type_hierarchical has to have an argument.
You know what helps? Not trying to use an object as an array. #facepalm
@ChuckReynolds Yep, capability, not compatibility. User capabilities only.
@ChuckReynolds I don't think there's such a thing as compatibility type for CPTs...
@ChuckReynolds Erm, I think that's capability type. I thought you were looking for hierarchical vs. non-hierarchical?
@ChuckReynolds @nacin What is compat as post? And no, that's the post post type. Can just use is_singular() without any args, I think.
@ChuckReynolds Try replacing is_singular('post') with is_single(), then inside that do if ( is_post_type_hierarchical( get_post_type() ) )
@ChuckReynolds Since it's OGP, you only want those particular tags on single anyway, right?
@ChuckReynolds Yeah then a combo of is_single && get_post_type and then is_post_type_hierarchical should do it, at least in my head :)
Thing I currently hate: Open Graph and Twitter's policy of never serving up email addresses via API, even with OAuth. Fake emails it is!!
@ChuckReynolds Ah, wp_head. Butterfingers :)
@ChuckReynolds If you do this using the wp_hook action, it should be fine in a plugin.
@ChuckReynolds I'll pretend I typed all that in 7 seconds ;)
@ChuckReynolds If the CPT might change, then you can use is_single and get_post_type() first to get the slug
@ChuckReynolds No need to reinvent the wheel, you can do is_singular('cpt-type') && is_post_type_hierarchical('cpt-slug')
@ChuckReynolds You should be able to get all that info in wp_head. Don't need to be in the loop or anything.
@ChuckReynolds @norcross I think is_singular() takes post type(s) as the argument. get_post_type() will get you the post type.
